    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail and slice your<strong> courgette[s]</strong> into discs</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-pollock-with-roast-veg-and-creamy-parsley-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>courgette discs</strong> and <strong>tomato wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 10 min or until the courgette has begun to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-pollock-with-roast-veg-and-creamy-parsley-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After the initial 10 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>onion wedges</strong>, then<strong> </strong>return to the oven for a further 15 min or until the potatoes are golden and crisp \u2013 this is your <strong>roasted veg</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-pollock-with-roast-veg-and-creamy-parsley-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-pollock-with-roast-veg-and-creamy-parsley-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>diced pollock</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-pollock-with-roast-veg-and-creamy-parsley-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced pollock</strong> and <strong>sliced garlic</strong> cook for 5 min, turning once half way, or until cooked through and crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>pan-fried pollock</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-pollock-with-roast-veg-and-creamy-parsley-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 40ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[60ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and stir in your <strong>soft cheese</strong></p><p>Add<strong> half </strong>the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy parsley sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pan-fried-pollock-with-roast-veg-and-creamy-parsley-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>roasted veg</strong> topped with the <strong>pan-fried pollock </strong>and any<strong> remaining pan juices</strong></p><p>Pour over the<strong> creamy parsley sauce </strong>and garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
